#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.5:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhaṇḍagāmavagga"
msgstr "1. At Bhaṇḍa Village"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Anusotasutta"
msgstr "5. With the Stream"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“These four people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an4.5:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. VAR: pāraṅgato → pāragato (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.5:1.3"
msgid ""
"Anusotagāmī puggalo, paṭisotagāmī puggalo, ṭhitatto puggalo, tiṇṇo pāraṅgato "
"thale tiṭṭhati brāhmaṇo."
msgstr ""
"A person who goes with the stream; a person who goes against the stream; a "
"steadfast person; and a brahmin who has crossed over and stands on the far "
"shore."

msgctxt "an4.5:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anusotagāmī puggalo?"
msgstr "And who is the person who goes with the stream?"

msgctxt "an4.5:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kāme ca paṭisevati, pāpañca kammaṃ karoti."
msgstr "It’s a person who takes part in sensual pleasures and does bad deeds."

msgctxt "an4.5:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anusotagāmī puggalo."
msgstr "This is called a person who goes with the stream."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paṭisotagāmī puggalo?"
msgstr "And who is the person who goes against the stream?"

# BB has “even” for -pli here, but the parallel phrasing at MN 46 shows that it just means “also”
msgctxt "an4.5:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kāme ca nappaṭisevati, pāpañca kammaṃ na "
"karoti, sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena assumukhopi rudamāno paripuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati."
msgstr ""
"It’s a person who doesn’t take part in sensual pleasures or do bad deeds. "
"They live the full and pure spiritual life in pain and sadness, weeping, "
"with tearful faces."

msgctxt "an4.5:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paṭisotagāmī puggalo."
msgstr "This is called a person who goes against the stream."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ṭhitatto puggalo?"
msgstr "And who is the steadfast person?"

msgctxt "an4.5:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha parinibbāyī, anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"It’s a person who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn "
"spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to return from "
"that world."

msgctxt "an4.5:3.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ṭhitatto puggalo."
msgstr "This is called a steadfast person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:4.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo tiṇṇo pāraṅgato thale tiṭṭhati brāhmaṇo?"
msgstr "And who is a brahmin who has crossed over and stands on the far shore?"

msgctxt "an4.5:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ "
"paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s a person who realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an4.5:4.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo tiṇṇo pāraṅgato thale tiṭṭhati brāhmaṇo."
msgstr ""
"This is called a brahmin who has crossed over and stands on the far shore."

msgctxt "an4.5:4.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti."
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:5.1"
msgid "Ye keci kāmesu asaññatā janā,"
msgstr "All those people with uncontrolled sensuality,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:5.2"
msgid "Avītarāgā idha kāmabhogino;"
msgstr "not free of lust, enjoying sensual pleasures in this life:"

#. <br>
#. VAR: jātijarūpagāmi te → jātijarūpagāhino (bj) | jātijarūpagā hi te (s1-3, km) | jātijarūpagāmī te (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.5:5.3"
msgid "Punappunaṃ jātijarūpagāmi te,"
msgstr "again and again, they return to birth and old age;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:5.4"
msgid "Taṇhādhipannā anusotagāmino."
msgstr "those who go with the stream are immersed in craving."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:6.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi dhīro idhupaṭṭhitassatī,"
msgstr "So a wise one in this life, with mindfulness established,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:6.2"
msgid "Kāme ca pāpe ca asevamāno;"
msgstr "doesn’t take part in sensual pleasures and bad deeds."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:6.3"
msgid "Sahāpi dukkhena jaheyya kāme,"
msgstr "In pain they’d give up sensual pleasures:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:6.4"
msgid "Paṭisotagāmīti tamāhu puggalaṃ."
msgstr "they call that person ‘one who goes against the stream’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:7.1"
msgid "Yo ve kilesāni pahāya pañca,"
msgstr "Someone who’s given up five corruptions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:7.2"
msgid "Paripuṇṇasekho aparihānadhammo;"
msgstr "a perfect trainee, not liable to decline,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:7.3"
msgid "Cetovasippatto samāhitindriyo,"
msgstr "who’s mastered their mind, with faculties immersed in samādhi,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:7.4"
msgid "Sa ve ṭhitattoti naro pavuccati."
msgstr "that’s called ‘a steadfast person’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.5:8.1"
msgid "Paroparā yassa samecca dhammā,"
msgstr "The sage who has comprehended all things, high and low,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:8.2"
msgid "Vidhūpitā atthagatā na santi;"
msgstr "cleared them and ended them, so they are no more;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Sa ve muni → sa vedagū (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.5:8.3"
msgid "Sa ve muni vusitabrahmacariyo,"
msgstr ""
"they’ve completed the spiritual journey, and gone to the end of the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.5:8.4"
msgid "Lokantagū pāragatoti vuccatī”ti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘one who has gone beyond’.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.5:8.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
